The paper discusses the use of visual cues and camera networks for surveillance, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) categories. The paper also addresses the challenges of understanding composite events and topological structure learning, which are related to system and control (cs.SY) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) categories. Finally, the paper discusses the use of tracking targets, which is related to robotics (cs.RO) category.
